      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "security: add Security Matrix runtime-fact audit model",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a Security Matrix runtime-fact evaluator.\n- Models actor, influence source, tool capability, approval state, and operator policy as separate inputs.\n- Adds default policy data, a deterministic evaluator, tool capability resolution, an audit-event object builder, tests, and documentation.\n- Adds a before-tool-call fact adapter and wires it into the trusted-tool-policy import path so the adapter is called with real tool-call facts during policy evaluation.\n- Removes the unsupported `security.matrix.audit.enabled` config gate, focused test, and docs reference.\n- Removes all Security Matrix dead-code allowlist entries — the production files are now reachable through the trusted-tool-policy import graph.\n- Hardens custom policy parsing so malformed decisions cannot weaken the default policy.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis PR remains non-enforcing and observe-only.\n\nIt does not block tool calls, require confirmation at runtime, emit runtime diagnostic events, change UI, change plugin behavior, or alter runtime tool execution. The before-tool-call adapter is called during trusted-policy evaluation to build the audit event shape from explicit boundary facts, but the result is not emitted. Runtime diagnostic emission, canonical config, CLI display, and enforcement remain future work.\n\n## Changes since last review\n\n- Wired `createSecurityMatrixBeforeToolCallAuditEvent` into `src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts` — imported and called during `runTrustedToolPolicies` with real `toolName` from the event. The Security Matrix production files are now reachable through the runtime import graph.\n- Removed all six Security Matrix files from both the required and optional Knip unused-file allowlists. The dead-code guard now sees them as used through the import path.\n- Removed `SecurityMatrixBeforeToolCallAuditConfig` type and `isSecurityMatrixBeforeToolCallAuditEnabled` function from `before-tool-call.ts`.\n- Deleted `src/agents/security-matrix-before-call.test.ts` (the config gate test).\n- Removed docs sentence naming `security.matrix.audit.enabled`.\n\n## Validation\n\nLatest head: `4ca5d4f8b2`.\n\nFocused commands run against this head:\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\npnpm test src/security/security-matrix/evaluate.test.ts\npnpm changed:lanes --base upstream/main --json\npnpm exec oxlint src/security/security-matrix/ src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts\nnode scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/security/security-matrix.md\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Security Matrix runtime-fact evaluation produces deterministic audit decisions from actor, influence source, capability, approval state, and operator policy. The before-tool-call adapter is wired into the trusted-tool-policy path and builds the audit event from real tool-call facts during policy evaluation. Malformed custom policy decisions are ignored. Custom policy overlays cannot weaken the default policy unless `allowPolicyWeakening` is explicitly set.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw development environment (Node.js 22, pnpm, Linux).\n\n### Evaluator output (10 scenarios, real policy data)\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n$ npx tsx /tmp/matrix-real-proof.mjs\n  PASS Agent exec with web influence (should block)\n    decision=block matched=policy reason=External content must not directly influence privileged local execution, credential access, or system configuration.\n  PASS User write_file with email influence (should require_confirm)\n    decision=require_confirm matched=policy reason=External content influencing state-changing actions should require explicit confirmation in future opt-in runtime modes.\n  PASS Agent git with github influence and approval (should allow)\n    decision=allow matched=approval_state reason=Explicit approval satisfied a require_confirm decision.\n  PASS User exec with no influence (should allow)\n    decision=allow matched=policy reason=No external-content influence is present; known capabilities defer to the existing operator tool policy.\n  PASS Agent exec with memory influence (should block)\n    decision=block matched=policy reason=External content must not directly influence privileged local execution, credential access, or system configuration.\n  PASS Unknown external influence + exec (should block)\n    decision=block matched=policy reason=External content must not directly influence privileged local execution, credential access, or system configuration.\n  PASS Custom policy without allowPolicyWeakening (cannot weaken)\n    decision=block matched=policy reason=A weaker custom decision was ignored.\n  PASS Custom policy with allowPolicyWeakening=true (can weaken)\n    decision=allow matched=policy reason=Policy decision matched without a rule reason.\n  PASS Malformed custom policy decision is ignored\n    decision=block matched=policy reason=External content must not directly influence privileged local execution, credential access, or system configuration.\n  PASS Capability resolution from tool name (exec -> exec capability)\n    decision=block matched=policy reason=External content must not directly influence privileged local execution, credential access, or system configuration.\n\n10 passed, 0 failed out of 10 scenarios\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Before-tool-call adapter output (3 scenarios, real facts)\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n$ npx tsx /tmp/matrix-adapter-proof.mjs\n  Full facts supplied: decision=block matched=policy approvalState=none\n  Minimal facts (defaults applied): decision=allow matched=policy approvalState=not_required\n  User actor with no influence: decision=allow matched=policy approvalState=not_required\n\nAll adapter scenarios produced valid audit events without emitting, blocking, or mutating execution.\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Unit tests, lint, docs, whitespace\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/security/security-matrix/evaluate.test.ts\n ✓ unit-fast src/security/security-matrix/evaluate.test.ts (27 tests) 13ms\n\n$ pnpm exec oxlint src/security/security-matrix/ src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\n\n$ node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/security/security-matrix.md\nDocs formatting clean (663 files).\n\n$ git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\n(no whitespace errors)\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nWhat was not tested: Runtime diagnostic emission, runtime enforcement, strict config schema adoption, CLI display, plugin UI, and live tool execution are intentionally not changed by this PR.",
